<TITLE> Court orders fugitive Dipjol's arrest </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 18 (bdnews24.com) A Dhaka court Tuesday ordered arrest of fugitive film actor and BNP ward commissioner Monwar Hossain Dipjol in a tax-dodge case. Judge Md Azizul Haque of Dhaka Metropolitan Special Judge's Court issued the arrest warrant against Dipjol, who had also been found guilty in two arms cases. National Board of Revenue deputy tax commissioner Mahtasibur Rahman Khan filed the case and testified before the court. According to case details, Dipjol evaded tax on Tk 12.14 crore earnings by concealing the amount when he had filed income tax returns for the period from Feb 25, 1991 to Oct 19, 2006. He violated the emergency powers rules by concealing and giving false information to tax authorities on lands bought and money deposited in banks in his and his sons' names, the case alleged. He has also been accused of holding back information on his four firearms, car, income from 22 films, rent from the buildings adjacent to Asia Cinema Hall and Deepnagar area and renovation of his paternal house. On July 26, Dipjol was sentenced to 17 years in jail for illegally keeping arms and ammunition. In another arms case, Dipjol and wife Romana Monwar, who is in jail, were handed down seven years on Aug 20. bdnew
